theorem Topology.dense_of_dense_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hDenseA : Dense A) (hAB : A ⊆ B) : Dense B := by
  -- `closure A = univ`, since `A` is dense.
  have hClosureA : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDenseA.closure_eq
  -- Monotonicity of `closure` under `subset`.
  have hSubset : closure A ⊆ closure B := closure_mono hAB
  -- Show `closure B = univ`.
  have hClosureB : closure B = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · -- Trivial inclusion.
      intro x _hx; simp
    · -- Every point belongs to `closure B`.
      intro x _hx
      -- From `closure A = univ`, we get `x ∈ closure A`.
      have hxA : x ∈ closure A := by
        simpa [hClosureA] using (by simp : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X))
      -- Monotonicity gives `x ∈ closure B`.
      exact hSubset hxA
  -- Reformulate the closure equality as density.
  simpa [Dense] using hClosureB
